1
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,307
Anybody home?
有人在家吗?

2
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:08,900
Hi.
你好.

3
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:10,900
Hi. Hi Danny.
你好.你好Danny.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,300
How you doing. Lisa?
你好吗,Lisa?

5
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,900
I found that video.
我找到那盘录像带了.

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,900
"Mars Needs Women". Excellent.
《火星需要女人》.非常好.

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,100
I looked everywhere for it,
我到处找这盘带子,

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,100
and I finally went to Video King.
最后在"录像大王"店里找到了.

9
00:00:25,470 --> 00:00:27,300
Michael, it is a great store.
Michael, 那是一家很不错的音像店.

10
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:29,900
Lisa, how long did you live in California?
Lisa,你在California住了多久?

11
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:32,000
My whole life until college. Why?
上大学之前一直住那儿.为什么?

12
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:36,900
I don't know. Maybe I should move to L.A.
我不知道.也许我该搬到洛杉矶去.

13
00:00:37,490 --> 00:00:38,800
What? Why?
什么?为什么?

14
00:00:38,910 --> 00:00:41,500
They have an excellent football team.
那里有一直很好的橄榄球队.

15
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:42,900
You're pathetic.
你真可怜.

16
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:45,800
Danny, you don't want to live in California.
Danny,你不会想住在California的.

17
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:47,600
It's one big disaster area.
那是一个充满灾难的地区.

18
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:49,800
So? So is my life.
那又怎么样?我的生活也是如此.

19
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:52,500
No. I mean things like floods.
不.我是指洪水之类的灾难.

20
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:58,400
And if it isn't a flood, it's a fire or an earthquake. Earthquakes, Danny.
如果不发洪水的话,也会有火灾, 或者地震.地震啊,Danny.

21
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,500
Have you ever been in one?
你经历过地震吗?

22
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:01,400
Plenty of times.
很多次了.

23
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:04,200
Most of them are small; you don't feel them.
大多数都是小地震,你感受不到.

24
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:05,800
But the one in 1990?
但1990年的那一次?

25
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:09,100
I was going into the airport and the ground started to move.
我正走进机场时, 大地开始震动.

26
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,090
People didn't want to stay in the airport, obviously,
人们不想待在机场里, 当然了,

27
00:01:12,190 --> 00:01:15,600
so they started running out of it, crying and screaming.
所以他们往机场外跑, 哭泣着, 尖叫着.

28
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:17,100
So?
那又怎么样呢?

29
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:21,900
The only disasters we have in New England are blizzards.
在新英格兰我们唯一的灾难是暴风雪.

30
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:23,700
And hurricanes.
还有飓风.

31
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,300
And hurricanes.
还有飓风.

32
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,800
And Danny's love life.
还有Danny的爱情生活.

33
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:29,800
Danny. Did you and Jeannette break up?
Danny.你和Jeannette分手了吗?

34
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,320
Yep. I dropped her like a hot potato.
是的.我像扔烫手山芋一样把她甩了.

35
00:01:33,450 --> 00:01:35,700
"Typhoon Danny and his Storm of Love", 
《台风Danny和他的爱情风暴》.

36
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,800
a new film by Michael Chung.
Michael Chung的新影片.

37
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:38,880
I like it.
我喜欢这个想法.

38
00:01:38,990 --> 00:01:42,100
Yeah, well, I'm charging you a fortune for the rights.
Yeah, well,那我可要向你收一大笔版权费.

